    <div class="post" id="jm">
        <h3>Jose Mourinho</h3>
        <p>
            Jose Mourinho is one of the most polarizing figures in the world of football. The self-proclaimed 'special one', grabs the headlines wherever he goes.
            Having won the treble with Inter Milan to breaking the points record in La Liga, Jose has made football history with his accomplishments.

            When Mourinho was asked "What is my idea of team?", he replied 'One where in a certain moment, faced with a certain situation, all of the players think the same way.
            This is my idea of a team. This is only possible with time, hard-work and composure.'
            He believes that the most important thing for a team is to have a certain model, certain principles, and to know and interpret them well, 
            regardless of the players that are being used.

            A corner stone of Mourinho's success as a manager has been his focus on tactical periodization. 
            Where the game can be broken into 4 moments: Offensive Organization, Attacking Transition, Defensive Transition and Defensive Organization.

            The objective of the offensive phase is to de-organize and unbalance the opponent's defensive structure with the 
            intention of creating and take advantage of spaces to allow the team to score goals. 

            As for the defensive stages the principle is to pressure over the ball and close down spaces, by taking advantage of the disorganization of the opponent's offensive shape 
            and thus recover the ball or organize the team defensively.
        </p>
