    <div class="post" id="jc">
        <h3>Johan Cryuff</h3>
        <p>
            In addition to his impressive career as a player and as a coach, Johan Cruyff was an innovator and football visionary. 
            Johan was the strongest advocate of beautiful football, relentlessly aiming to produce both quality and results. 
            He argued that football, in its very essence, is a game intended to entertain and bring joy to the fans. 
            Johan’s distinctive philosophy on talent development, in which individual development is the cornerstone of an academy, gave birth to generations of great players and coaches. 
            They continue to dominate the game of football today and are the living proof of an unrivalled personal football legacy.

            Cryuff always considered aesthetic and moral aspects of the game, 
            "winning is an important thing, but to have your own style, to have people copy you, to admire you, that is the greatest gift". 

            He compiled a list of 14 rules which encapuslate his football philosophy:
            1) Team Player 2) Responsbility 3) Respect 4) Integration 5) Initiative 6) Coaching 7) Personality 
            8) Social Involvement 9) Technique 10) Tactics 11) Development 12) Learning 13) Play Together 14) Creativity
        </p>
